The paper deals with distribution testing, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The use of modular reduction-based approach and $\ell_2$-identity tester suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The information-theoretic approach used for lower bounds suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of sample-optimal testers and matching sample lower bounds suggests that the paper may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC, and cs.SI, in that order.
